headliner: Three Kings Night - A Latin Dance Celebration
notes: NOCHE DE REYES! Y REINAS! Our Second Annual THREE KING’SNIGHT. It’s the first opportunity in the year to enjoy, sing and dance with friends and family in a very special Three Kings Day’s celebration. A Latin traditional event that commemorates the three kings’ journey to the manger to present the baby Jesus with three symbolic gifts (Epiphany) aka Latin Christmas. The party starts at 9PM so come and get your spot early. Polish your moves with dance lessons by a local Latin dance instructor and jump right into the dance floor to dance to the best of Salsa, Merengue, Bachata, Cumbias, Regetton and much more with DJ Rudy Max! This is an EXCLUSIVE LATIN NIGHT series brought to you by Cultura Latina Magazine & TallyBreeze so join us and immerse yourselves in our authentic Latin Culture.

Eric Gales is an American blues-rock guitarist, originally hailed as a child prodigy. As of 2018 Gales has recorded seventeen albums for major record labels and has done session and tribute work. He has also contributed vocals on several records by the Memphis rap groups Prophet Posse and Three 6 Mafia under the name Lil E. Gales picked up the guitar at age four and was playing in blues competitions by the age of 10. Although Gales plays a right-handed guitar "upside-down" (with the bass E string on the bottom), he is not naturally left-handed; he was taught by his brother, who is left-handed, and never second-guessed the untraditional technique.
